race.comment: OLIVIA ROSE (6) is a consistent 4yo mare who is racing in fine form, racing wide on speed last start at Pakenham but coming away in a strongly run race to win well. She gets a much better scenario here from the low gate and can notch up another victory. GRINZINGER POD (5) was just fair last time at Wangaratta but had been good in two runs prior and can figure if she can find her best. WRITTEN BLIGH (2) was okay in a bunched finish last start. She can roll forward and give a sight. TRIAL BY PRESS (1) has won first up and over 1200m. She'll get further but has the ability to be sprinting well fresh.
